<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-1847] ByteBufferUtil.clone shouldn&apos;t mutate the passed bytebuffer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1847</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently ByteBufferUtil.clone uses .mark and .reset on the passed ByteBuffer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is fine when using thrift because no two ByteBuffer are being accessed at the same time, but this could be thread-unsafe if the same BB was passed concurrently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solandra is having problems with this (Solandra shares JVM with Cassandra).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12493038">CASSANDRA-1847</key>
