                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12970683" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 02:13:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 uses arraycopy instead of manual loop and enforces non-null&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970751" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 08:59:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on v2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970814" author="tjake" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 14:00:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right, thats faster but I was thinking ahead for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1714&quot; title=&quot;zero-copy reads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1714&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1714&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we&apos;d need to use this for putting a row into the cache and .array() only works with HeapByteBuffers.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970821" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 14:49:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;should we add an instanceof check for HeapByteBuffer then? seems like it&apos;s probably worth it. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970835" author="tjake" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 15:04:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v3 checks if buffer isDirect()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970887" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 16:44:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;BB.get&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/information.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; adds arrayoffset to the given index, so I think the loop in v3 is buggy.  v4 attached&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970893" author="tjake" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 16:52:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok took &quot;absolute&quot; too literally then &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
+1 v4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970895" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 16:56:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970901" author="hudson" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2010 17:14:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.7 #72 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/72/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/72/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    make ByteBufferUtil.clone thread-safe&lt;br/&gt;
patch by tjake and jbellis for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1847&quot; title=&quot;ByteBufferUtil.clone shouldn&amp;#39;t mutate the passed bytebuffer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1847&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1847&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
